# How to Run the Project with Docker (Quick Guide)

## Prerequisites
- Git
- Docker & Docker Compose

# Create the .env file from the example
# Then, edit the .env file and add your API key.
# It should contain: MISTRAL_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxx

## Build & Run Commands

# Build the Docker image (run this once initially)
docker-compose build

# Run the application
docker-compose up

# Access the app in your browser at:
# http://localhost:8501

## Other Commands

# Run in the background (detached)
docker-compose up -d

# View logs (if running in detached mode)
docker-compose logs -f

# Stop and remove the container
docker-compose down